      "message": "housekeeping may be not the best word. In Python gae_ts_mon the same cron job sends both metrics collected from appengine instances and global metrics (like this one). Buildbucket also sends the \"state of the world\":\nhttps://cs.chromium.org/chromium/infra/appengine/cr-buildbucket/metrics.py?q\u003dcr-buildbucket/metrics\u0026sq\u003dpackage:chromium\u0026l\u003d256\n\nthis function registered in\n\nhttps://cs.chromium.org/chromium/infra/appengine/cr-buildbucket/main.py?type\u003dcs\u0026q\u003dupdate_global_metrics\u0026sq\u003dpackage:chromium\u0026l\u003d39\n\nThere might be a technical reason for that, I remember sergeyberezin gave a long explanation involving implementation details of gae_ts_mon. Anyway, he is on 4w vacation. I hope this will work, we may want to check with him when he is back.",
